page.title: 12Atlantic College Students
page.content: When Atlantic College first started in 1962 there were 12 countries represented.They were Brazil,Canada, Denmark,France,Germany,Greece, Netherlands,Norway,Sweden,U.S.A., Switzerland and United Kingdom. In 1985 there were 57 countries represented.They were Argentina, Australia,Austria,Bahamas,Belguim, Bermuda,Botswana,Canada,Cayman Island,Chile,Colombia,Denmark,Fiji, Finland,France,West Germany,Ghana, Greece,Guernsey,Hong Kong,Hungary, India,Indonesia,Isle of Man,Israel, Italy,Japan,Jamaica,Jersey,Jordan, Kenya,Korea,Lebanon,Lesotho,Mexico, Namibia,Netherlands,N.Zealand,Spain, Nigeria,Norway,Panama,Peru,Poland, Portugal,Senegal,Singapore,S.Africa, Swaziland,Sweden,Switzerland,U.K., U.S.A.,Venezuela,Yugoslavia,Zambia and Zimbabwe.
